President Barack Obama has proclaimed March 2014 as American Red Cross Month. In his proclamation, he honors the work of the American Red Cross and other relief organizations that provide assistance and support to those in need. He recognizes the importance of their efforts in bringing relief, hope, and healing to those affected by disasters and war. The President also highlights the unity and compassion displayed by Americans during times of crisis and encourages all Americans to observe this month by supporting the work of service and relief organizations.